  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Assessment of the mutational profile of the residual clone and the distribution of lymphocyte
      subpopulations at 3 years of treatment with ibrutinib

      This project has an epidemiological part: to establish the percentage of patients, in a
      real-life situation, still undergoing treatment 3 years after its initiation, as well as a
      biological part: to determine the evolution of the clone and the prevalence of BTK mutations
      and PLCg2 in the absence of clinical or biological criteria for scalability.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
